2605 /// Maps command line option to frontend action.
2606 static std::optional<frontend::ActionKind>
2607 getFrontendAction(OptSpecifier &Opt) {
2608  for (const auto &ActionOpt : getFrontendActionTable())
2609  if (ActionOpt.second == Opt.getID())
2610  return ActionOpt.first;
2611 
2612  return std::nullopt;
2613 }
2614 
2615 /// Maps frontend action to command line option.
2616 static std::optional<OptSpecifier>
2617 getProgramActionOpt(frontend::ActionKind ProgramAction) {
2618  for (const auto &ActionOpt : getFrontendActionTable())
2619  if (ActionOpt.first == ProgramAction)
2620  return OptSpecifier(ActionOpt.second);
2621 
2622  return std::nullopt;
2623 }
2624 
2625 static void GenerateFrontendArgs(const FrontendOptions &Opts,
2626  ArgumentConsumer Consumer, bool IsHeader) {
2627  const FrontendOptions &FrontendOpts = Opts;
2628 #define FRONTEND_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(...) \
2629  GENERATE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(Consumer, __VA_ARGS__)
2630 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
2631 #undef FRONTEND_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
2632 
2633  std::optional<OptSpecifier> ProgramActionOpt =
2634  getProgramActionOpt(Opts.ProgramAction);
2635 
2636  // Generating a simple flag covers most frontend actions.
2637  std::function<void()> GenerateProgramAction = [&]() {
2638  GenerateArg(Consumer, *ProgramActionOpt);
2639  };
2640 
2641  if (!ProgramActionOpt) {
2642  // PluginAction is the only program action handled separately.
2643  assert(Opts.ProgramAction == frontend::PluginAction &&
2644  "Frontend action without option.");
2645  GenerateProgramAction = [&]() {
2646  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_plugin, Opts.ActionName);
2647  };
2648  }
2649 
2650  // FIXME: Simplify the complex 'AST dump' command line.
2651  if (Opts.ProgramAction == frontend::ASTDump) {
2652  GenerateProgramAction = [&]() {
2653  // ASTDumpLookups, ASTDumpDeclTypes and ASTDumpFilter are generated via
2654  // marshalling infrastructure.
2655 
2656  if (Opts.ASTDumpFormat != ADOF_Default) {
2657  StringRef Format;
2658  switch (Opts.ASTDumpFormat) {
2659  case ADOF_Default:
2660  llvm_unreachable("Default AST dump format.");
2661  case ADOF_JSON:
2662  Format = "json";
2663  break;
2664  }
2665 
2666  if (Opts.ASTDumpAll)
2667  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ast_dump_all_EQ, Format);
2668  if (Opts.ASTDumpDecls)
2669  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ast_dump_EQ, Format);
2670  } else {
2671  if (Opts.ASTDumpAll)
2672  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ast_dump_all);
2673  if (Opts.ASTDumpDecls)
2674  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ast_dump);
2675  }
2676  };
2677  }
2678 
2679  if (Opts.ProgramAction == frontend::FixIt && !Opts.FixItSuffix.empty()) {
2680  GenerateProgramAction = [&]() {
2681  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fixit_EQ, Opts.FixItSuffix);
2682  };
2683  }
2684 
2685  GenerateProgramAction();
2686 
2687  for (const auto &PluginArgs : Opts.PluginArgs) {
2688  Option Opt = getDriverOptTable().getOption(OPT_plugin_arg);
2689  for (const auto &PluginArg : PluginArgs.second)
2690  denormalizeString(Consumer,
2691  Opt.getPrefix() + Opt.getName() + PluginArgs.first,
2692  Opt.getKind(), 0, PluginArg);
2693  }
2694 
2695  for (const auto &Ext : Opts.ModuleFileExtensions)
2696  if (auto *TestExt = dyn_cast_or_null<TestModuleFileExtension>(Ext.get()))
2697  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ftest_module_file_extension_EQ, TestExt->str());
2698 
2699  if (!Opts.CodeCompletionAt.FileName.empty())
2700  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_code_completion_at,
2701  Opts.CodeCompletionAt.ToString());
2702 
2703  for (const auto &Plugin : Opts.Plugins)
2704  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_load, Plugin);
2705 
2706  // ASTDumpDecls and ASTDumpAll already handled with ProgramAction.
2707 
2708  for (const auto &ModuleFile : Opts.ModuleFiles)
2709  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fmodule_file, ModuleFile);
2710 
2711  if (Opts.AuxTargetCPU)
2712  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_aux_target_cpu, *Opts.AuxTargetCPU);
2713 
2714  if (Opts.AuxTargetFeatures)
2715  for (const auto &Feature : *Opts.AuxTargetFeatures)
2716  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_aux_target_feature, Feature);
2717 
2718  {
2719  StringRef Preprocessed = Opts.DashX.isPreprocessed() ? "-cpp-output" : "";
2720  StringRef ModuleMap =
2721  Opts.DashX.getFormat() == InputKind::ModuleMap ? "-module-map" : "";
2722  StringRef HeaderUnit = "";
2723  switch (Opts.DashX.getHeaderUnitKind()) {
2724  case InputKind::HeaderUnit_None:
2725  break;
2726  case InputKind::HeaderUnit_User:
2727  HeaderUnit = "-user";
2728  break;
2729  case InputKind::HeaderUnit_System:
2730  HeaderUnit = "-system";
2731  break;
2732  case InputKind::HeaderUnit_Abs:
2733  HeaderUnit = "-header-unit";
2734  break;
2735  }
2736  StringRef Header = IsHeader ? "-header" : "";
2737 
2738  StringRef Lang;
2739  switch (Opts.DashX.getLanguage()) {
2740  case Language::C:
2741  Lang = "c";
2742  break;
2743  case Language::OpenCL:
2744  Lang = "cl";
2745  break;
2746  case Language::OpenCLCXX:
2747  Lang = "clcpp";
2748  break;
2749  case Language::CUDA:
2750  Lang = "cuda";
2751  break;
2752  case Language::HIP:
2753  Lang = "hip";
2754  break;
2755  case Language::CXX:
2756  Lang = "c++";
2757  break;
2758  case Language::ObjC:
2759  Lang = "objective-c";
2760  break;
2761  case Language::ObjCXX:
2762  Lang = "objective-c++";
2763  break;
2764  case Language::RenderScript:
2765  Lang = "renderscript";
2766  break;
2767  case Language::Asm:
2768  Lang = "assembler-with-cpp";
2769  break;
2770  case Language::Unknown:
2771  assert(Opts.DashX.getFormat() == InputKind::Precompiled &&
2772  "Generating -x argument for unknown language (not precompiled).");
2773  Lang = "ast";
2774  break;
2775  case Language::LLVM_IR:
2776  Lang = "ir";
2777  break;
2778  case Language::HLSL:
2779  Lang = "hlsl";
2780  break;
2781  case Language::CIR:
2782  Lang = "cir";
2783  break;
2784  }
2785 
2786  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_x,
2787  Lang + HeaderUnit + Header + ModuleMap + Preprocessed);
2788  }
2789 
2790  // OPT_INPUT has a unique class, generate it directly.
2791  for (const auto &Input : Opts.Inputs)
2792  Consumer(Input.getFile());
2793 }
2794 
2795 static bool ParseFrontendArgs(FrontendOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
2796  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags, bool &IsHeaderFile) {
2797  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
2798 
2799  FrontendOptions &FrontendOpts = Opts;
2800 
2801 #define FRONTEND_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(...) \
2802  PARSE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(Args, Diags, __VA_ARGS__)
2803 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
2804 #undef FRONTEND_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
2805 
2806  Opts.ProgramAction = frontend::ParseSyntaxOnly;
2807  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_Action_Group)) {
2808  OptSpecifier Opt = OptSpecifier(A->getOption().getID());
2809  std::optional<frontend::ActionKind> ProgramAction = getFrontendAction(Opt);
2810  assert(ProgramAction && "Option specifier not in Action_Group.");
2811 
2812  if (ProgramAction == frontend::ASTDump &&
2813  (Opt == OPT_ast_dump_all_EQ || Opt == OPT_ast_dump_EQ)) {
2814  unsigned Val = llvm::StringSwitch<unsigned>(A->getValue())
2815  .CaseLower("default", ADOF_Default)
2816  .CaseLower("json", ADOF_JSON)
2817  .Default(std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max());
2818 
2819  if (Val != std::numeric_limits<unsigned>::max())
2820  Opts.ASTDumpFormat = static_cast<ASTDumpOutputFormat>(Val);
2821  else {
2822  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
2823  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
2824  Opts.ASTDumpFormat = ADOF_Default;
2825  }
2826  }
2827 
2828  if (ProgramAction == frontend::FixIt && Opt == OPT_fixit_EQ)
2829  Opts.FixItSuffix = A->getValue();
2830 
2831  if (ProgramAction == frontend::GenerateInterfaceStubs) {
2832  StringRef ArgStr =
2833  Args.hasArg(OPT_interface_stub_version_EQ)
2834  ? Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_interface_stub_version_EQ)
2835  : "ifs-v1";
2836  if (ArgStr == "experimental-yaml-elf-v1" ||
2837  ArgStr == "experimental-ifs-v1" || ArgStr == "experimental-ifs-v2" ||
2838  ArgStr == "experimental-tapi-elf-v1") {
2839  std::string ErrorMessage =
2840  "Invalid interface stub format: " + ArgStr.str() +
2841  " is deprecated.";
2842  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
2843  << "Must specify a valid interface stub format type, ie: "
2844  "-interface-stub-version=ifs-v1"
2845  << ErrorMessage;
2846  ProgramAction = frontend::ParseSyntaxOnly;
2847  } else if (!ArgStr.starts_with("ifs-")) {
2848  std::string ErrorMessage =
2849  "Invalid interface stub format: " + ArgStr.str() + ".";
2850  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
2851  << "Must specify a valid interface stub format type, ie: "
2852  "-interface-stub-version=ifs-v1"
2853  << ErrorMessage;
2854  ProgramAction = frontend::ParseSyntaxOnly;
2855  }
2856  }
2857 
2858  Opts.ProgramAction = *ProgramAction;
2859  }
2860 
2861  if (const Arg* A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_plugin)) {
2862  Opts.Plugins.emplace_back(A->getValue(0));
2863  Opts.ProgramAction = frontend::PluginAction;
2864  Opts.ActionName = A->getValue();
2865  }
2866  for (const auto *AA : Args.filtered(OPT_plugin_arg))
2867  Opts.PluginArgs[AA->getValue(0)].emplace_back(AA->getValue(1));
2868 
2869  for (const std::string &Arg :
2870  Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_ftest_module_file_extension_EQ)) {
2871  std::string BlockName;
2872  unsigned MajorVersion;
2873  unsigned MinorVersion;
2874  bool Hashed;
2875  std::string UserInfo;
2876  if (parseTestModuleFileExtensionArg(Arg, BlockName, MajorVersion,
2877  MinorVersion, Hashed, UserInfo)) {
2878  Diags.Report(diag::err_test_module_file_extension_format) << Arg;
2879 
2880  continue;
2881  }
2882 
2883  // Add the testing module file extension.
2884  Opts.ModuleFileExtensions.push_back(
2885  std::make_shared<TestModuleFileExtension>(
2886  BlockName, MajorVersion, MinorVersion, Hashed, UserInfo));
2887  }
2888 
2889  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_code_completion_at)) {
2890  Opts.CodeCompletionAt =
2891  ParsedSourceLocation::FromString(A->getValue());
2892  if (Opts.CodeCompletionAt.FileName.empty())
2893  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
2894  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
2895  }
2896 
2897  Opts.Plugins = Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_load);
2898  Opts.ASTDumpDecls = Args.hasArg(OPT_ast_dump, OPT_ast_dump_EQ);
2899  Opts.ASTDumpAll = Args.hasArg(OPT_ast_dump_all, OPT_ast_dump_all_EQ);
2900  // Only the -fmodule-file=<file> form.
2901  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fmodule_file)) {
2902  StringRef Val = A->getValue();
2903  if (!Val.contains('='))
2904  Opts.ModuleFiles.push_back(std::string(Val));
2905  }
2906 
2907  if (Opts.ProgramAction != frontend::GenerateModule && Opts.IsSystemModule)
2908  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_argument_only_allowed_with) << "-fsystem-module"
2909  << "-emit-module";
2910 
2911  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_aux_target_cpu))
2912  Opts.AuxTargetCPU = std::string(Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_aux_target_cpu));
2913  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_aux_target_feature))
2914  Opts.AuxTargetFeatures = Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_aux_target_feature);
2915 
2916  if (Opts.ARCMTAction != FrontendOptions::ARCMT_None &&
2917  Opts.ObjCMTAction != FrontendOptions::ObjCMT_None) {
2918  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
2919  << "ARC migration" << "ObjC migration";
2920  }
2921 
2922  InputKind DashX(Language::Unknown);
2923  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_x)) {
2924  StringRef XValue = A->getValue();
2925 
2926  // Parse suffixes:
2927  // '<lang>(-[{header-unit,user,system}-]header|[-module-map][-cpp-output])'.
2928  // FIXME: Supporting '<lang>-header-cpp-output' would be useful.
2929  bool Preprocessed = XValue.consume_back("-cpp-output");
2930  bool ModuleMap = XValue.consume_back("-module-map");
2931  // Detect and consume the header indicator.
2932  bool IsHeader =
2933  XValue != "precompiled-header" && XValue.consume_back("-header");
2934 
2935  // If we have c++-{user,system}-header, that indicates a header unit input
2936  // likewise, if the user put -fmodule-header together with a header with an
2937  // absolute path (header-unit-header).
2938  InputKind::HeaderUnitKind HUK = InputKind::HeaderUnit_None;
2939  if (IsHeader || Preprocessed) {
2940  if (XValue.consume_back("-header-unit"))
2941  HUK = InputKind::HeaderUnit_Abs;
2942  else if (XValue.consume_back("-system"))
2943  HUK = InputKind::HeaderUnit_System;
2944  else if (XValue.consume_back("-user"))
2945  HUK = InputKind::HeaderUnit_User;
2946  }
2947 
2948  // The value set by this processing is an un-preprocessed source which is
2949  // not intended to be a module map or header unit.
2950  IsHeaderFile = IsHeader && !Preprocessed && !ModuleMap &&
2951  HUK == InputKind::HeaderUnit_None;
2952 
2953  // Principal languages.
2954  DashX = llvm::StringSwitch<InputKind>(XValue)
2955  .Case("c", Language::C)
2956  .Case("cl", Language::OpenCL)
2957  .Case("clcpp", Language::OpenCLCXX)
2958  .Case("cuda", Language::CUDA)
2959  .Case("hip", Language::HIP)
2960  .Case("c++", Language::CXX)
2961  .Case("objective-c", Language::ObjC)
2962  .Case("objective-c++", Language::ObjCXX)
2963  .Case("renderscript", Language::RenderScript)
2964  .Case("hlsl", Language::HLSL)
2965  .Default(Language::Unknown);
2966 
2967  // "objc[++]-cpp-output" is an acceptable synonym for
2968  // "objective-c[++]-cpp-output".
2969  if (DashX.isUnknown() && Preprocessed && !IsHeaderFile && !ModuleMap &&
2970  HUK == InputKind::HeaderUnit_None)
2971  DashX = llvm::StringSwitch<InputKind>(XValue)
2972  .Case("objc", Language::ObjC)
2973  .Case("objc++", Language::ObjCXX)
2974  .Default(Language::Unknown);
2975 
2976  // Some special cases cannot be combined with suffixes.
2977  if (DashX.isUnknown() && !Preprocessed && !IsHeaderFile && !ModuleMap &&
2978  HUK == InputKind::HeaderUnit_None)
2979  DashX = llvm::StringSwitch<InputKind>(XValue)
2980  .Case("cpp-output", InputKind(Language::C).getPreprocessed())
2981  .Case("assembler-with-cpp", Language::Asm)
2982  .Cases("ast", "pcm", "precompiled-header",
2983  InputKind(Language::Unknown, InputKind::Precompiled))
2984  .Case("ir", Language::LLVM_IR)
2985  .Case("cir", Language::CIR)
2986  .Default(Language::Unknown);
2987 
2988  if (DashX.isUnknown())
2989  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
2990  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
2991 
2992  if (Preprocessed)
2993  DashX = DashX.getPreprocessed();
2994  // A regular header is considered mutually exclusive with a header unit.
2995  if (HUK != InputKind::HeaderUnit_None) {
2996  DashX = DashX.withHeaderUnit(HUK);
2997  IsHeaderFile = true;
2998  } else if (IsHeaderFile)
2999  DashX = DashX.getHeader();
3000  if (ModuleMap)
3001  DashX = DashX.withFormat(InputKind::ModuleMap);
3002  }
3003 
3004  // '-' is the default input if none is given.
3005  std::vector<std::string> Inputs = Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_INPUT);
3006  Opts.Inputs.clear();
3007  if (Inputs.empty())
3008  Inputs.push_back("-");
3009 
3010  if (DashX.getHeaderUnitKind() != InputKind::HeaderUnit_None &&
3011  Inputs.size() > 1)
3012  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_header_unit_extra_inputs) << Inputs[1];
3013 
3014  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Inputs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
3015  InputKind IK = DashX;
3016  if (IK.isUnknown()) {
3017  IK = FrontendOptions::getInputKindForExtension(
3018  StringRef(Inputs[i]).rsplit('.').second);
3019  // FIXME: Warn on this?
3020  if (IK.isUnknown())
3021  IK = Language::C;
3022  // FIXME: Remove this hack.
3023  if (i == 0)
3024  DashX = IK;
3025  }
3026 
3027  bool IsSystem = false;
3028 
3029  // The -emit-module action implicitly takes a module map.
3030  if (Opts.ProgramAction == frontend::GenerateModule &&
3031  IK.getFormat() == InputKind::Source) {
3032  IK = IK.withFormat(InputKind::ModuleMap);
3033  IsSystem = Opts.IsSystemModule;
3034  }
3035 
3036  Opts.Inputs.emplace_back(std::move(Inputs[i]), IK, IsSystem);
3037  }
3038 
3039  Opts.DashX = DashX;
3040 
3041  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
3042 }

3044 std::string CompilerInvocation::GetResourcesPath(const char *Argv0,
3045  void *MainAddr) {
3046  std::string ClangExecutable =
3047  llvm::sys::fs::getMainExecutable(Argv0, MainAddr);
3048  return Driver::GetResourcesPath(ClangExecutable, CLANG_RESOURCE_DIR);
3049 }

3051 static void GenerateHeaderSearchArgs(const HeaderSearchOptions &Opts,
3052  ArgumentConsumer Consumer) {
3053  const HeaderSearchOptions *HeaderSearchOpts = &Opts;
3054 #define HEADER_SEARCH_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(...) \
3055  GENERATE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(Consumer, __VA_ARGS__)
3056 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
3057 #undef HEADER_SEARCH_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
3058 
3059  if (Opts.UseLibcxx)
3060  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_stdlib_EQ, "libc++");
3061 
3062  if (!Opts.ModuleCachePath.empty())
3063  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fmodules_cache_path, Opts.ModuleCachePath);
3064 
3065  for (const auto &File : Opts.PrebuiltModuleFiles)
3066  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fmodule_file, File.first + "=" + File.second);
3067 
3068  for (const auto &Path : Opts.PrebuiltModulePaths)
3069  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fprebuilt_module_path, Path);
3070 
3071  for (const auto &Macro : Opts.ModulesIgnoreMacros)
3072  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fmodules_ignore_macro, Macro.val());
3073 
3074  auto Matches = [](const HeaderSearchOptions::Entry &Entry,
3075  llvm::ArrayRef<frontend::IncludeDirGroup> Groups,
3076  std::optional<bool> IsFramework,
3077  std::optional<bool> IgnoreSysRoot) {
3078  return llvm::is_contained(Groups, Entry.Group) &&
3079  (!IsFramework || (Entry.IsFramework == *IsFramework)) &&
3080  (!IgnoreSysRoot || (Entry.IgnoreSysRoot == *IgnoreSysRoot));
3081  };
3082 
3083  auto It = Opts.UserEntries.begin();
3084  auto End = Opts.UserEntries.end();
3085 
3086  // Add -I..., -F..., and -index-header-map options in order.
3087  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::IndexHeaderMap, frontend::Angled},
3088  std::nullopt, true);
3089  ++It) {
3090  OptSpecifier Opt = [It, Matches]() {
3091  if (Matches(*It, frontend::IndexHeaderMap, true, true))
3092  return OPT_F;
3093  if (Matches(*It, frontend::IndexHeaderMap, false, true))
3094  return OPT_I;
3095  if (Matches(*It, frontend::Angled, true, true))
3096  return OPT_F;
3097  if (Matches(*It, frontend::Angled, false, true))
3098  return OPT_I;
3099  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected HeaderSearchOptions::Entry.");
3100  }();
3101 
3102  if (It->Group == frontend::IndexHeaderMap)
3103  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_index_header_map);
3104  GenerateArg(Consumer, Opt, It->Path);
3105  };
3106 
3107  // Note: some paths that came from "[-iprefix=xx] -iwithprefixbefore=yy" may
3108  // have already been generated as "-I[xx]yy". If that's the case, their
3109  // position on command line was such that this has no semantic impact on
3110  // include paths.
3111  for (; It < End &&
3112  Matches(*It, {frontend::After, frontend::Angled}, false, true);
3113  ++It) {
3114  OptSpecifier Opt =
3115  It->Group == frontend::After ? OPT_iwithprefix : OPT_iwithprefixbefore;
3116  GenerateArg(Consumer, Opt, It->Path);
3117  }
3118 
3119  // Note: Some paths that came from "-idirafter=xxyy" may have already been
3120  // generated as "-iwithprefix=xxyy". If that's the case, their position on
3121  // command line was such that this has no semantic impact on include paths.
3122  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::After}, false, true); ++It)
3123  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_idirafter, It->Path);
3124  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::Quoted}, false, true); ++It)
3125  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_iquote, It->Path);
3126  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::System}, false, std::nullopt);
3127  ++It)
3128  GenerateArg(Consumer, It->IgnoreSysRoot ? OPT_isystem : OPT_iwithsysroot,
3129  It->Path);
3130  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::System}, true, true); ++It)
3131  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_iframework, It->Path);
3132  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::System}, true, false); ++It)
3133  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_iframeworkwithsysroot, It->Path);
3134 
3135  // Add the paths for the various language specific isystem flags.
3136  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::CSystem}, false, true); ++It)
3137  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_c_isystem, It->Path);
3138  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::CXXSystem}, false, true); ++It)
3139  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_cxx_isystem, It->Path);
3140  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::ObjCSystem}, false, true); ++It)
3141  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_objc_isystem, It->Path);
3142  for (; It < End && Matches(*It, {frontend::ObjCXXSystem}, false, true); ++It)
3143  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_objcxx_isystem, It->Path);
3144 
3145  // Add the internal paths from a driver that detects standard include paths.
3146  // Note: Some paths that came from "-internal-isystem" arguments may have
3147  // already been generated as "-isystem". If that's the case, their position on
3148  // command line was such that this has no semantic impact on include paths.
3149  for (; It < End &&
3150  Matches(*It, {frontend::System, frontend::ExternCSystem}, false, true);
3151  ++It) {
3152  OptSpecifier Opt = It->Group == frontend::System
3153  ? OPT_internal_isystem
3154  : OPT_internal_externc_isystem;
3155  GenerateArg(Consumer, Opt, It->Path);
3156  }
3157 
3158  assert(It == End && "Unhandled HeaderSearchOption::Entry.");
3159 
3160  // Add the path prefixes which are implicitly treated as being system headers.
3161  for (const auto &P : Opts.SystemHeaderPrefixes) {
3162  OptSpecifier Opt = P.IsSystemHeader ? OPT_system_header_prefix
3163  : OPT_no_system_header_prefix;
3164  GenerateArg(Consumer, Opt, P.Prefix);
3165  }
3166 
3167  for (const std::string &F : Opts.VFSOverlayFiles)
3168  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ivfsoverlay, F);
3169 }
3170 
3171 static bool ParseHeaderSearchArgs(HeaderSearchOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
3172  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
3173  const std::string &WorkingDir) {
3174  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
3175 
3176  HeaderSearchOptions *HeaderSearchOpts = &Opts;
3177 
3178 #define HEADER_SEARCH_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(...) \
3179  PARSE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(Args, Diags, __VA_ARGS__)
3180 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
3181 #undef HEADER_SEARCH_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
3182 
3183  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_stdlib_EQ))
3184  Opts.UseLibcxx = (strcmp(A->getValue(), "libc++") == 0);
3185 
3186  // Canonicalize -fmodules-cache-path before storing it.
3187  SmallString<128> P(Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_fmodules_cache_path));
3188  if (!(P.empty() || llvm::sys::path::is_absolute(P))) {
3189  if (WorkingDir.empty())
3190  llvm::sys::fs::make_absolute(P);
3191  else
3192  llvm::sys::fs::make_absolute(WorkingDir, P);
3193  }
3194  llvm::sys::path::remove_dots(P);
3195  Opts.ModuleCachePath = std::string(P);
3196 
3197  // Only the -fmodule-file=<name>=<file> form.
3198  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fmodule_file)) {
3199  StringRef Val = A->getValue();
3200  if (Val.contains('=')) {
3201  auto Split = Val.split('=');
3202  Opts.PrebuiltModuleFiles.insert_or_assign(
3203  std::string(Split.first), std::string(Split.second));
3204  }
3205  }
3206  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fprebuilt_module_path))
3207  Opts.AddPrebuiltModulePath(A->getValue());
3208 
3209  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_fmodules_ignore_macro)) {
3210  StringRef MacroDef = A->getValue();
3211  Opts.ModulesIgnoreMacros.insert(
3212  llvm::CachedHashString(MacroDef.split('=').first));
3213  }
3214 
3215  // Add -I..., -F..., and -index-header-map options in order.
3216  bool IsIndexHeaderMap = false;
3217  bool IsSysrootSpecified =
3218  Args.hasArg(OPT__sysroot_EQ) || Args.hasArg(OPT_isysroot);
3219 
3220  // Expand a leading `=` to the sysroot if one was passed (and it's not a
3221  // framework flag).
3222  auto PrefixHeaderPath = [IsSysrootSpecified,
3223  &Opts](const llvm::opt::Arg *A,
3224  bool IsFramework = false) -> std::string {
3225  assert(A->getNumValues() && "Unexpected empty search path flag!");
3226  if (IsSysrootSpecified && !IsFramework && A->getValue()[0] == '=') {
3227  SmallString<32> Buffer;
3228  llvm::sys::path::append(Buffer, Opts.Sysroot,
3229  llvm::StringRef(A->getValue()).substr(1));
3230  return std::string(Buffer);
3231  }
3232  return A->getValue();
3233  };
3234 
3235  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_I, OPT_F, OPT_index_header_map)) {
3236  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_index_header_map)) {
3237  // -index-header-map applies to the next -I or -F.
3238  IsIndexHeaderMap = true;
3239  continue;
3240  }
3241 
3242  frontend::IncludeDirGroup Group =
3243  IsIndexHeaderMap ? frontend::IndexHeaderMap : frontend::Angled;
3244 
3245  bool IsFramework = A->getOption().matches(OPT_F);
3246  Opts.AddPath(PrefixHeaderPath(A, IsFramework), Group, IsFramework,
3247  /*IgnoreSysroot*/ true);
3248  IsIndexHeaderMap = false;
3249  }
3250 
3251  // Add -iprefix/-iwithprefix/-iwithprefixbefore options.
3252  StringRef Prefix = ""; // FIXME: This isn't the correct default prefix.
3253  for (const auto *A :
3254  Args.filtered(OPT_iprefix, OPT_iwithprefix, OPT_iwithprefixbefore)) {
3255  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_iprefix))
3256  Prefix = A->getValue();
3257  else if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_iwithprefix))
3258  Opts.AddPath(Prefix.str() + A->getValue(), frontend::After, false, true);
3259  else
3260  Opts.AddPath(Prefix.str() + A->getValue(), frontend::Angled, false, true);
3261  }
3262 
3263  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_idirafter))
3264  Opts.AddPath(PrefixHeaderPath(A), frontend::After, false, true);
3265  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_iquote))
3266  Opts.AddPath(PrefixHeaderPath(A), frontend::Quoted, false, true);
3267 
3268  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_isystem, OPT_iwithsysroot)) {
3269  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_iwithsysroot)) {
3270  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::System, false,
3271  /*IgnoreSysRoot=*/false);
3272  continue;
3273  }
3274  Opts.AddPath(PrefixHeaderPath(A), frontend::System, false, true);
3275  }
3276  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_iframework))
3277  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::System, true, true);
3278  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_iframeworkwithsysroot))
3279  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::System, /*IsFramework=*/true,
3280  /*IgnoreSysRoot=*/false);
3281 
3282  // Add the paths for the various language specific isystem flags.
3283  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_c_isystem))
3284  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::CSystem, false, true);
3285  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_cxx_isystem))
3286  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::CXXSystem, false, true);
3287  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_objc_isystem))
3288  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::ObjCSystem, false,true);
3289  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_objcxx_isystem))
3290  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), frontend::ObjCXXSystem, false, true);
3291 
3292  // Add the internal paths from a driver that detects standard include paths.
3293  for (const auto *A :
3294  Args.filtered(OPT_internal_isystem, OPT_internal_externc_isystem)) {
3295  frontend::IncludeDirGroup Group = frontend::System;
3296  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_internal_externc_isystem))
3297  Group = frontend::ExternCSystem;
3298  Opts.AddPath(A->getValue(), Group, false, true);
3299  }
3300 
3301  // Add the path prefixes which are implicitly treated as being system headers.
3302  for (const auto *A :
3303  Args.filtered(OPT_system_header_prefix, OPT_no_system_header_prefix))
3304  Opts.AddSystemHeaderPrefix(
3305  A->getValue(), A->getOption().matches(OPT_system_header_prefix));
3306 
3307  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_ivfsoverlay, OPT_vfsoverlay))
3308  Opts.AddVFSOverlayFile(A->getValue());
3309 
3310  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
3311 }

3314  ArgumentConsumer Consumer) {
3315  if (!Opts.SwiftVersion.empty())
3316  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fapinotes_swift_version,
3317  Opts.SwiftVersion.getAsString());
3318

3320  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_iapinotes_modules, Path);
3321 }

3323 static void ParseAPINotesArgs(APINotesOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
3324  DiagnosticsEngine &diags) {
3325  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_fapinotes_swift_version)) {
3326  if (Opts.SwiftVersion.tryParse(A->getValue()))
3327  diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
3328  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
3329  }
3330  for (const Arg *A : Args.filtered(OPT_iapinotes_modules))
3331  Opts.ModuleSearchPaths.push_back(A->getValue());

3344 
3345 /// Check if input file kind and language standard are compatible.
3346 static bool IsInputCompatibleWithStandard(InputKind IK,
3347  const LangStandard &S) {
3348  switch (IK.getLanguage()) {
3349  case Language::Unknown:
3350  case Language::LLVM_IR:
3351  case Language::CIR:
3352  llvm_unreachable("should not parse language flags for this input");
3353 
3354  case Language::C:
3355  case Language::ObjC:
3356  case Language::RenderScript:
3357  return S.getLanguage() == Language::C;
3358 
3359  case Language::OpenCL:
3360  return S.getLanguage() == Language::OpenCL ||
3361  S.getLanguage() == Language::OpenCLCXX;
3362 
3363  case Language::OpenCLCXX:
3364  return S.getLanguage() == Language::OpenCLCXX;
3365 
3366  case Language::CXX:
3367  case Language::ObjCXX:
3368  return S.getLanguage() == Language::CXX;
3369 
3370  case Language::CUDA:
3371  // FIXME: What -std= values should be permitted for CUDA compilations?
3372  return S.getLanguage() == Language::CUDA ||
3373  S.getLanguage() == Language::CXX;
3374 
3375  case Language::HIP:
3376  return S.getLanguage() == Language::CXX || S.getLanguage() == Language::HIP;
3377 
3378  case Language::Asm:
3379  // Accept (and ignore) all -std= values.
3380  // FIXME: The -std= value is not ignored; it affects the tokenization
3381  // and preprocessing rules if we're preprocessing this asm input.
3382  return true;
3383 
3384  case Language::HLSL:
3385  return S.getLanguage() == Language::HLSL;
3386  }
3387 
3388  llvm_unreachable("unexpected input language");
3389 }
3390 
3391 /// Get language name for given input kind.
3392 static StringRef GetInputKindName(InputKind IK) {
3393  switch (IK.getLanguage()) {
3394  case Language::C:
3395  return "C";
3396  case Language::ObjC:
3397  return "Objective-C";
3398  case Language::CXX:
3399  return "C++";
3400  case Language::ObjCXX:
3401  return "Objective-C++";
3402  case Language::OpenCL:
3403  return "OpenCL";
3404  case Language::OpenCLCXX:
3405  return "C++ for OpenCL";
3406  case Language::CUDA:
3407  return "CUDA";
3408  case Language::RenderScript:
3409  return "RenderScript";
3410  case Language::HIP:
3411  return "HIP";
3412 
3413  case Language::Asm:
3414  return "Asm";
3415  case Language::LLVM_IR:
3416  return "LLVM IR";
3417  case Language::CIR:
3418  return "Clang IR";
3419 
3420  case Language::HLSL:
3421  return "HLSL";
3422 
3423  case Language::Unknown:
3424  break;
3425  }
3426  llvm_unreachable("unknown input language");
3427 }

3429 void CompilerInvocationBase::GenerateLangArgs(const LangOptions &Opts,
3430  ArgumentConsumer Consumer,
3431  const llvm::Triple &T,
3432  InputKind IK) {
3433  if (IK.getFormat() == InputKind::Precompiled ||
3434  IK.getLanguage() == Language::LLVM_IR ||
3435  IK.getLanguage() == Language::CIR) {
3436  if (Opts.ObjCAutoRefCount)
3437  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fobjc_arc);
3438  if (Opts.PICLevel != 0)
3439  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_pic_level, Twine(Opts.PICLevel));
3440  if (Opts.PIE)
3441  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_pic_is_pie);
3442  for (StringRef Sanitizer : serializeSanitizerKinds(Opts.Sanitize))
3443  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fsanitize_EQ, Sanitizer);
3444  if (!Opts.OptRecordFile.empty())
3445  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_opt_record_file, Opts.OptRecordFile);
3446 
3447  return;
3448  }
3449 
3450  OptSpecifier StdOpt;
3451  switch (Opts.LangStd) {
3452  case LangStandard::lang_opencl10:
3453  case LangStandard::lang_opencl11:
3454  case LangStandard::lang_opencl12:
3455  case LangStandard::lang_opencl20:
3456  case LangStandard::lang_opencl30:
3457  case LangStandard::lang_openclcpp10:
3458  case LangStandard::lang_openclcpp2021:
3459  StdOpt = OPT_cl_std_EQ;
3460  break;
3461  default:
3462  StdOpt = OPT_std_EQ;
3463  break;
3464  }
3465 
3466  auto LangStandard = LangStandard::getLangStandardForKind(Opts.LangStd);
3467  GenerateArg(Consumer, StdOpt, LangStandard.getName());
3468 
3469  if (Opts.IncludeDefaultHeader)
3470  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_finclude_default_header);
3471  if (Opts.DeclareOpenCLBuiltins)
3472  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fdeclare_opencl_builtins);
3473 
3474  const LangOptions *LangOpts = &Opts;
3475 
3476 #define LANG_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(...) \
3477  GENERATE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(Consumer, __VA_ARGS__)
3478 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
3479 #undef LANG_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
3480 
3481  if (!Opts.FPAccuracyVal.empty())
3482  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ffp_builtin_accuracy_EQ, Opts.FPAccuracyVal);
3483 
3484  for (const auto &F : Opts.FPAccuracyFuncMap)
3485  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ffp_builtin_accuracy_EQ,
3486  (F.second + ":" + F.first));
3487 
3488  // The '-fcf-protection=' option is generated by CodeGenOpts generator.
3489 
3490  if (Opts.ObjC) {
3491  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fobjc_runtime_EQ, Opts.ObjCRuntime.getAsString());
3492 
3493  if (Opts.GC == LangOptions::GCOnly)
3494  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fobjc_gc_only);
3495  else if (Opts.GC == LangOptions::HybridGC)
3496  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fobjc_gc);
3497  else if (Opts.ObjCAutoRefCount == 1)
3498  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fobjc_arc);
3499 
3500  if (Opts.ObjCWeakRuntime)
3501  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fobjc_runtime_has_weak);
3502 
3503  if (Opts.ObjCWeak)
3504  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fobjc_weak);
3505 
3506  if (Opts.ObjCSubscriptingLegacyRuntime)
3507  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fobjc_subscripting_legacy_runtime);
3508  }
3509 
3510  if (Opts.GNUCVersion != 0) {
3511  unsigned Major = Opts.GNUCVersion / 100 / 100;
3512  unsigned Minor = (Opts.GNUCVersion / 100) % 100;
3513  unsigned Patch = Opts.GNUCVersion % 100;
3514  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fgnuc_version_EQ,
3515  Twine(Major) + "." + Twine(Minor) + "." + Twine(Patch));
3516  }
3517 
3518  if (Opts.IgnoreXCOFFVisibility)
3519  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_mignore_xcoff_visibility);
3520 
3521  if (Opts.SignedOverflowBehavior == LangOptions::SOB_Trapping) {
3522  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ftrapv);
3523  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ftrapv_handler, Opts.OverflowHandler);
3524  } else if (Opts.SignedOverflowBehavior == LangOptions::SOB_Defined) {
3525  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fwrapv);
3526  }
3527 
3528  if (Opts.MSCompatibilityVersion != 0) {
3529  unsigned Major = Opts.MSCompatibilityVersion / 10000000;
3530  unsigned Minor = (Opts.MSCompatibilityVersion / 100000) % 100;
3531  unsigned Subminor = Opts.MSCompatibilityVersion % 100000;
3532  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fms_compatibility_version,
3533  Twine(Major) + "." + Twine(Minor) + "." + Twine(Subminor));
3534  }
3535 
3536  if ((!Opts.GNUMode && !Opts.MSVCCompat && !Opts.CPlusPlus17 && !Opts.C23) ||
3537  T.isOSzOS()) {
3538  if (!Opts.Trigraphs)
3539  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fno_trigraphs);
3540  } else {
3541  if (Opts.Trigraphs)
3542  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ftrigraphs);
3543  }
3544 
3545  if (Opts.Blocks && !(Opts.OpenCL && Opts.OpenCLVersion == 200))
3546  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fblocks);
3547 
3548  if (Opts.ConvergentFunctions &&
3549  !(Opts.OpenCL || (Opts.CUDA && Opts.CUDAIsDevice) || Opts.SYCLIsDevice ||
3550  Opts.HLSL))
3551  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fconvergent_functions);
3552 
3553  if (Opts.NoBuiltin && !Opts.Freestanding)
3554  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fno_builtin);
3555 
3556  if (!Opts.NoBuiltin)
3557  for (const auto &Func : Opts.NoBuiltinFuncs)
3558  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fno_builtin_, Func);
3559 
3560  if (Opts.LongDoubleSize == 128)
3561  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_mlong_double_128);
3562  else if (Opts.LongDoubleSize == 64)
3563  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_mlong_double_64);
3564  else if (Opts.LongDoubleSize == 80)
3565  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_mlong_double_80);
3566 
3567  // Not generating '-mrtd', it's just an alias for '-fdefault-calling-conv='.
3568 
3569  // OpenMP was requested via '-fopenmp', not implied by '-fopenmp-simd' or
3570  // '-fopenmp-targets='.
3571  if (Opts.OpenMP && !Opts.OpenMPSimd) {
3572  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp);
3573 
3574  if (Opts.OpenMP != 51)
3575  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_version_EQ, Twine(Opts.OpenMP));
3576 
3577  if (!Opts.OpenMPUseTLS)
3578  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fnoopenmp_use_tls);
3579 
3580  if (Opts.OpenMPIsTargetDevice)
3581  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_is_target_device);
3582 
3583  if (Opts.OpenMPIRBuilder)
3584  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_enable_irbuilder);
3585  }
3586 
3587  if (Opts.OpenMPSimd) {
3588  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_simd);
3589 
3590  if (Opts.OpenMP != 51)
3591  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_version_EQ, Twine(Opts.OpenMP));
3592  }
3593 
3594  if (Opts.OpenMPThreadSubscription)
3595  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_assume_threads_oversubscription);
3596 
3597  if (Opts.OpenMPTeamSubscription)
3598  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_assume_teams_oversubscription);
3599 
3600  if (Opts.OpenMPTargetDebug != 0)
3601  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_target_debug_EQ,
3602  Twine(Opts.OpenMPTargetDebug));
3603 
3604  if (Opts.OpenMPCUDANumSMs != 0)
3605  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_cuda_number_of_sm_EQ,
3606  Twine(Opts.OpenMPCUDANumSMs));
3607 
3608  if (Opts.OpenMPCUDABlocksPerSM != 0)
3609  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_cuda_blocks_per_sm_EQ,
3610  Twine(Opts.OpenMPCUDABlocksPerSM));
3611 
3612  if (Opts.OpenMPCUDAReductionBufNum != 1024)
3613  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_cuda_teams_reduction_recs_num_EQ,
3614  Twine(Opts.OpenMPCUDAReductionBufNum));
3615 
3616  if (!Opts.OMPTargetTriples.empty()) {
3617  std::string Targets;
3618  llvm::raw_string_ostream OS(Targets);
3619  llvm::interleave(
3620  Opts.OMPTargetTriples, OS,
3621  [&OS](const llvm::Triple &T) { OS << T.str(); }, ",");
3622  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_targets_EQ, OS.str());
3623  }
3624 
3625  if (!Opts.OMPHostIRFile.empty())
3626  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_host_ir_file_path, Opts.OMPHostIRFile);
3627 
3628  if (Opts.OpenMPCUDAMode)
3629  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenmp_cuda_mode);
3630 
3631  if (Opts.OpenACC) {
3632  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fopenacc);
3633  if (!Opts.OpenACCMacroOverride.empty())
3634  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_openacc_macro_override,
3635  Opts.OpenACCMacroOverride);
3636  }
3637 
3638  // The arguments used to set Optimize, OptimizeSize and NoInlineDefine are
3639  // generated from CodeGenOptions.
3640 
3641  if (Opts.DefaultFPContractMode == LangOptions::FPM_Fast)
3642  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ffp_contract, "fast");
3643  else if (Opts.DefaultFPContractMode == LangOptions::FPM_On)
3644  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ffp_contract, "on");
3645  else if (Opts.DefaultFPContractMode == LangOptions::FPM_Off)
3646  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ffp_contract, "off");
3647  else if (Opts.DefaultFPContractMode == LangOptions::FPM_FastHonorPragmas)
3648  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ffp_contract, "fast-honor-pragmas");
3649 
3650  for (StringRef Sanitizer : serializeSanitizerKinds(Opts.Sanitize))
3651  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fsanitize_EQ, Sanitizer);
3652 
3653  // Conflating '-fsanitize-system-ignorelist' and '-fsanitize-ignorelist'.
3654  for (const std::string &F : Opts.NoSanitizeFiles)
3655  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fsanitize_ignorelist_EQ, F);
3656 
3657  switch (Opts.getClangABICompat()) {
3658  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver3_8:
3659  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ, "3.8");
3660  break;
3661  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver4:
3662  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ, "4.0");
3663  break;
3664  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver6:
3665  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ, "6.0");
3666  break;
3667  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver7:
3668  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ, "7.0");
3669  break;
3670  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver9:
3671  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ, "9.0");
3672  break;
3673  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver11:
3674  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ, "11.0");
3675  break;
3676  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver12:
3677  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ, "12.0");
3678  break;
3679  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver14:
3680  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ, "14.0");
3681  break;
3682  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver15:
3683  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ, "15.0");
3684  break;
3685  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver17:
3686  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ, "17.0");
3687  break;
3688  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver18:
3689  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ, "18.0");
3690  break;
3691  case LangOptions::ClangABI::Latest:
3692  break;
3693  }
3694 
3695  if (Opts.getSignReturnAddressScope() ==
3696  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressScopeKind::All)
3697  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_msign_return_address_EQ, "all");
3698  else if (Opts.getSignReturnAddressScope() ==
3699  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressScopeKind::NonLeaf)
3700  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_msign_return_address_EQ, "non-leaf");
3701 
3702  if (Opts.getSignReturnAddressKey() ==
3703  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressKeyKind::BKey)
3704  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_msign_return_address_key_EQ, "b_key");
3705 
3706  if (Opts.CXXABI)
3707  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fcxx_abi_EQ,
3708  TargetCXXABI::getSpelling(*Opts.CXXABI));
3709 
3710  if (Opts.RelativeCXXABIVTables)
3711  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fexperimental_relative_cxx_abi_vtables);
3712  else
3713  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fno_experimental_relative_cxx_abi_vtables);
3714 
3715  switch (Opts.getDefaultSubGroupSizeType()) {
3716  case LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Auto:
3717  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fsycl_default_sub_group_size, "automatic");
3718  break;
3719  case LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Primary:
3720  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fsycl_default_sub_group_size, "primary");
3721  break;
3722  case LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Integer:
3723  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fsycl_default_sub_group_size,
3724  Twine(Opts.DefaultSubGroupSize));
3725  break;
3726  case LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::None:
3727  break;
3728  }
3729 
3730  if (Opts.isSYCL()) {
3731  switch (Opts.SYCLVersion) {
3732  case LangOptions::SYCL_2017:
3733  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_sycl_std_EQ, "2017");
3734  break;
3735  case LangOptions::SYCL_2020:
3736  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_sycl_std_EQ, "2020");
3737  break;
3738  case LangOptions::SYCL_None:
3739  // Do nothing, case where we were given an invalid value.
3740  break;
3741  }
3742  }
3743  if (Opts.UseTargetPathSeparator)
3744  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_ffile_reproducible);
3745  else
3746  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fno_file_reproducible);
3747 
3748  for (const auto &MP : Opts.MacroPrefixMap)
3749  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fmacro_prefix_map_EQ, MP.first + "=" + MP.second);
3750 
3751  if (!Opts.RandstructSeed.empty())
3752  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_frandomize_layout_seed_EQ, Opts.RandstructSeed);
3753 
3754  if (!Opts.GPURelocatableDeviceCode)
3755  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fno_gpu_rdc);
3756 }
3757 
3758 static void checkFPAccuracyIsValid(StringRef ValElement,
3759  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags) {
3760  if (!llvm::StringSwitch<bool>(ValElement)
3761  .Case("default", true)
3762  .Case("high", true)
3763  .Case("low", true)
3764  .Case("medium", true)
3765  .Case("sycl", true)
3766  .Case("cuda", true)
3767  .Default(false))
3768  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_unsupported_option_argument)
3769  << "-ffp-accuracy" << ValElement;
3770 }
3771 
3772 static void diagnoseFPAccuracyHasVal(DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
3773  StringRef ValElement, StringRef Opt1,
3774  StringRef Opt2, const std::string Func) {
3775  Diags.Report(diag::warn_drv_fp_accuracy_override) << Opt1 << Opt2 << Func;
3776 }
3777 
3778 void CompilerInvocation::ParseFpAccuracyArgs(LangOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
3779  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags) {
3780  for (StringRef Values : Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_ffp_builtin_accuracy_EQ)) {
3781  if (Opts.MathErrno) {
3782  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_incompatible_fp_accuracy_options);
3783  } else {
3784  SmallVector<StringRef, 8> ValuesArr;
3785  Values.split(ValuesArr, ' ');
3786  for (const auto &Val : ValuesArr) {
3787  SmallVector<StringRef, 3> ValElement;
3788  Val.split(ValElement, ':');
3789  // The option is of the form -ffp-accuracy=value.
3790  if (ValElement.size() == 1) {
3791  checkFPAccuracyIsValid(ValElement[0], Diags);
3792  Opts.FPAccuracyVal = ValElement[0].str();
3793  // if FPAccuracyFuncMap is not empty, visit it and update
3794  // the values of the FPAccuracy of each function in the map;
3795  // last fp-accuracy option in the command line wins.
3796  for (auto &F : Opts.FPAccuracyFuncMap) {
3797  diagnoseFPAccuracyHasVal(Diags, ValElement[0], ValuesArr[1],
3798  ValuesArr[0], F.first);
3799  F.second = ValElement[0];
3800  }
3801  }
3802  // The option is of the form -ffp-accuracy=value:[f1, ... fn].
3803  if (ValElement.size() == 2) {
3804  SmallVector<StringRef, 30> FuncList;
3805  ValElement[1].split(FuncList, ',');
3806  for (StringRef FuncName : FuncList) {
3807  if (FuncName.front() == '[')
3808  FuncName = FuncName.drop_front(1);
3809  if (FuncName.back() == ']')
3810  FuncName = FuncName.drop_back(1);
3811  checkFPAccuracyIsValid(ValElement[0], Diags);
3812  // No need to fill the map if the FPaccuracy is 'default'.
3813  // The default builtin will be generated.
3814  if (!ValElement[0].equals("default")) {
3815  // if FPAccuracyFuncMap of this function has been previously set
3816  // update its value; the last fp-accuracy option in the command
3817  // line wins.
3818  auto FuncMap = Opts.FPAccuracyFuncMap.find(FuncName.str());
3819  if (FuncMap != Opts.FPAccuracyFuncMap.end()) {
3820  diagnoseFPAccuracyHasVal(Diags, ValElement[0], ValuesArr[1],
3821  ValuesArr[0], FuncMap->first.c_str());
3822  FuncMap->second = ValElement[0].str();
3823  } else {
3824  Opts.FPAccuracyFuncMap.insert(
3825  {FuncName.str(), ValElement[0].str()});
3826  }
3827  }
3828  }
3829  }
3830  }
3831  }
3832  }
3833 }
3834 
3835 bool CompilerInvocation::ParseLangArgs(LangOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
3836  InputKind IK, const llvm::Triple &T,
3837  std::vector<std::string> &Includes,
3838  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags) {
3839  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
3840 
3841  if (IK.getFormat() == InputKind::Precompiled ||
3842  IK.getLanguage() == Language::LLVM_IR ||
3843  IK.getLanguage() == Language::CIR) {
3844  // ObjCAAutoRefCount and Sanitize LangOpts are used to setup the
3845  // PassManager in BackendUtil.cpp. They need to be initialized no matter
3846  // what the input type is.
3847  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fobjc_arc))
3848  Opts.ObjCAutoRefCount = 1;
3849  // PICLevel and PIELevel are needed during code generation and this should
3850  // be set regardless of the input type.
3851  Opts.PICLevel = getLastArgIntValue(Args, OPT_pic_level, 0, Diags);
3852  Opts.PIE = Args.hasArg(OPT_pic_is_pie);
3853  parseSanitizerKinds("-fsanitize=", Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_fsanitize_EQ),
3854  Diags, Opts.Sanitize);
3855 
3856  // OptRecordFile is used to generate the optimization record file should
3857  // be set regardless of the input type.
3858  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_opt_record_file))
3859  Opts.OptRecordFile =
3860  std::string(Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_opt_record_file));
3861 
3862  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
3863  }
3864 
3865  // Other LangOpts are only initialized when the input is not AST or LLVM IR.
3866  // FIXME: Should we really be parsing this for an Language::Asm input?
3867 
3868  // FIXME: Cleanup per-file based stuff.
3869  LangStandard::Kind LangStd = LangStandard::lang_unspecified;
3870  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_std_EQ)) {
3871  LangStd = LangStandard::getLangKind(A->getValue());
3872  if (LangStd == LangStandard::lang_unspecified) {
3873  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
3874  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
3875  // Report supported standards with short description.
3876  for (unsigned KindValue = 0;
3877  KindValue != LangStandard::lang_unspecified;
3878  ++KindValue) {
3879  const LangStandard &Std = LangStandard::getLangStandardForKind(
3880  static_cast<LangStandard::Kind>(KindValue));
3881  if (IsInputCompatibleWithStandard(IK, Std)) {
3882  auto Diag = Diags.Report(diag::note_drv_use_standard);
3883  Diag << Std.getName() << Std.getDescription();
3884  unsigned NumAliases = 0;
3885 #define LANGSTANDARD(id, name, lang, desc, features)
3886 #define LANGSTANDARD_ALIAS(id, alias) \
3887  if (KindValue == LangStandard::lang_##id) ++NumAliases;
3888 #define LANGSTANDARD_ALIAS_DEPR(id, alias)
3889 #include "clang/Basic/LangStandards.def"
3890  Diag << NumAliases;
3891 #define LANGSTANDARD(id, name, lang, desc, features)
3892 #define LANGSTANDARD_ALIAS(id, alias) \
3893  if (KindValue == LangStandard::lang_##id) Diag << alias;
3894 #define LANGSTANDARD_ALIAS_DEPR(id, alias)
3895 #include "clang/Basic/LangStandards.def"
3896  }
3897  }
3898  } else {
3899  // Valid standard, check to make sure language and standard are
3900  // compatible.
3901  const LangStandard &Std = LangStandard::getLangStandardForKind(LangStd);
3902  if (!IsInputCompatibleWithStandard(IK, Std)) {
3903  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_argument_not_allowed_with)
3904  << A->getAsString(Args) << GetInputKindName(IK);
3905  }
3906  }
3907  }
3908 
3909  // -cl-std only applies for OpenCL language standards.
3910  // Override the -std option in this case.
3911  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_cl_std_EQ)) {
3912  LangStandard::Kind OpenCLLangStd
3913  = llvm::StringSwitch<LangStandard::Kind>(A->getValue())
3914  .Cases("cl", "CL", LangStandard::lang_opencl10)
3915  .Cases("cl1.0", "CL1.0", LangStandard::lang_opencl10)
3916  .Cases("cl1.1", "CL1.1", LangStandard::lang_opencl11)
3917  .Cases("cl1.2", "CL1.2", LangStandard::lang_opencl12)
3918  .Cases("cl2.0", "CL2.0", LangStandard::lang_opencl20)
3919  .Cases("cl3.0", "CL3.0", LangStandard::lang_opencl30)
3920  .Cases("clc++", "CLC++", LangStandard::lang_openclcpp10)
3921  .Cases("clc++1.0", "CLC++1.0", LangStandard::lang_openclcpp10)
3922  .Cases("clc++2021", "CLC++2021", LangStandard::lang_openclcpp2021)
3923  .Default(LangStandard::lang_unspecified);
3924 
3925  if (OpenCLLangStd == LangStandard::lang_unspecified) {
3926  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
3927  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
3928  }
3929  else
3930  LangStd = OpenCLLangStd;
3931  }
3932 
3933  // We have to parse this manually before the marshalling, otherwise we can't
3934  // use the marshalling to set other flags based on the SYCL version.
3935  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fsycl_is_device) || Args.hasArg(OPT_fsycl_is_host)) {
3936  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_sycl_std_EQ)) {
3937  Opts.setSYCLVersion(
3938  llvm::StringSwitch<LangOptions::SYCLMajorVersion>(A->getValue())
3939  .Case("2020", LangOptions::SYCL_2020)
3940  .Cases("2017", "121", "1.2.1", "sycl-1.2.1",
3941  LangOptions::SYCL_2017)
3942  .Default(LangOptions::SYCL_None));
3943 
3944  if (Opts.SYCLVersion == LangOptions::SYCL_None)
3945  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
3946  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
3947  } else {
3948  // If the user supplied -fsycl-is-device or -fsycl-is-host, but failed to
3949  // provide -sycl-std=, we want to default it to whatever the default SYCL
3950  // version is.
3951  Opts.setSYCLVersion(LangOptions::SYCL_Default);
3952  }
3953  }
3954 
3955  // Parse SYCL Default Sub group size.
3956  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_fsycl_default_sub_group_size)) {
3957  StringRef Value = A->getValue();
3958  Opts.setDefaultSubGroupSizeType(
3959  llvm::StringSwitch<LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType>(Value)
3960  .Case("automatic", LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Auto)
3961  .Case("primary", LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Primary)
3962  .Default(LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Integer));
3963 
3964  if (Opts.getDefaultSubGroupSizeType() ==
3965  LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::Integer) {
3966  int64_t IntResult;
3967  if (!Value.getAsInteger(10, IntResult)) {
3968  Opts.DefaultSubGroupSize = IntResult;
3969  } else {
3970  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
3971  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
3972  Opts.setDefaultSubGroupSizeType(LangOptions::SubGroupSizeType::None);
3973  }
3974  }
3975  }
3976 
3977  // These need to be parsed now. They are used to set OpenCL defaults.
3978  Opts.IncludeDefaultHeader = Args.hasArg(OPT_finclude_default_header);
3979  Opts.DeclareOpenCLBuiltins = Args.hasArg(OPT_fdeclare_opencl_builtins);
3980 
3981  LangOptions::setLangDefaults(Opts, IK.getLanguage(), T, Includes, LangStd);
3982 
3983  // The key paths of codegen options defined in Options.td start with
3984  // "LangOpts->". Let's provide the expected variable name and type.
3985  LangOptions *LangOpts = &Opts;
3986 
3987 #define LANG_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(...) \
3988  PARSE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(Args, Diags, __VA_ARGS__)
3989 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
3990 #undef LANG_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
3991 
3992  ParseFpAccuracyArgs(Opts, Args, Diags);
3993 
3994  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_fcf_protection_EQ)) {
3995  StringRef Name = A->getValue();
3996  if (Name == "full" || Name == "branch") {
3997  Opts.CFProtectionBranch = 1;
3998  }
3999  }
4000 
4001  if (Opts.ObjC) {
4002  if (Arg *arg = Args.getLastArg(OPT_fobjc_runtime_EQ)) {
4003  StringRef value = arg->getValue();
4004  if (Opts.ObjCRuntime.tryParse(value))
4005  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_unknown_objc_runtime) << value;
4006  }
4007 
4008  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fobjc_gc_only))
4009  Opts.setGC(LangOptions::GCOnly);
4010  else if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fobjc_gc))
4011  Opts.setGC(LangOptions::HybridGC);
4012  else if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fobjc_arc)) {
4013  Opts.ObjCAutoRefCount = 1;
4014  if (!Opts.ObjCRuntime.allowsARC())
4015  Diags.Report(diag::err_arc_unsupported_on_runtime);
4016  }

4018  // ObjCWeakRuntime tracks whether the runtime supports __weak, not
4019  // whether the feature is actually enabled. This is predominantly
4020  // determined by -fobjc-runtime, but we allow it to be overridden
4021  // from the command line for testing purposes.
4022  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fobjc_runtime_has_weak))
4023  Opts.ObjCWeakRuntime = 1;
4024  else
4025  Opts.ObjCWeakRuntime = Opts.ObjCRuntime.allowsWeak();
4026 
4027  // ObjCWeak determines whether __weak is actually enabled.
4028  // Note that we allow -fno-objc-weak to disable this even in ARC mode.
4029  if (auto weakArg = Args.getLastArg(OPT_fobjc_weak, OPT_fno_objc_weak)) {
4030  if (!weakArg->getOption().matches(OPT_fobjc_weak)) {
4031  assert(!Opts.ObjCWeak);
4032  } else if (Opts.getGC() != LangOptions::NonGC) {
4033  Diags.Report(diag::err_objc_weak_with_gc);

4035  Diags.Report(diag::err_objc_weak_unsupported);
4036  } else {

4038  }
4039  } else if (Opts.ObjCAutoRefCount) {
4040  Opts.ObjCWeak = Opts.ObjCWeakRuntime;
4041  }

4049  // Check that the version has 1 to 3 components and the minor and patch
4050  // versions fit in two decimal digits.

4052  bool Invalid = GNUCVer.tryParse(A->getValue());
4053  unsigned Major = GNUCVer.getMajor();
4054  unsigned Minor = GNUCVer.getMinor().value_or(0);
4055  unsigned Patch = GNUCVer.getSubminor().value_or(0);
4056  if (Invalid || GNUCVer.getBuild() || Minor >= 100 || Patch >= 100) {
4057  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
4058  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();

4061  }

4063  if (T.isOSAIX() && (Args.hasArg(OPT_mignore_xcoff_visibility)))

4093  Opts.Trigraphs =

4097  && Opts.OpenCLVersion == 200);

4100  Opts.OpenCL || (Opts.CUDA && Opts.CUDAIsDevice) ||
4101  Opts.SYCLIsDevice || Opts.HLSL;
4102 
4103  Opts.NoBuiltin = Args.hasArg(OPT_fno_builtin) || Opts.Freestanding;
4104  if (!Opts.NoBuiltin)
4105  getAllNoBuiltinFuncValues(Args, Opts.NoBuiltinFuncs);
4106  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_LongDouble_Group)) {
4107  if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mlong_double_64))
4108  Opts.LongDoubleSize = 64;
4109  else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mlong_double_80))
4110  Opts.LongDoubleSize = 80;
4111  else if (A->getOption().matches(options::OPT_mlong_double_128))

4113  else

4278 
4279  // This is the __NO_INLINE__ define, which just depends on things like the

4281  // inlining enabled.

4283  if (Arg *InlineArg = Args.getLastArg(
4284  options::OPT_finline_functions, options::OPT_finline_hint_functions,
4285  options::OPT_fno_inline_functions, options::OPT_fno_inline))

4288 
4289  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_ffp_contract)) {
4290  StringRef Val = A->getValue();
4291  if (Val == "fast")
4292  Opts.setDefaultFPContractMode(LangOptions::FPM_Fast);
4293  else if (Val == "on")
4294  Opts.setDefaultFPContractMode(LangOptions::FPM_On);
4295  else if (Val == "off")
4296  Opts.setDefaultFPContractMode(LangOptions::FPM_Off);
4297  else if (Val == "fast-honor-pragmas")
4298  Opts.setDefaultFPContractMode(LangOptions::FPM_FastHonorPragmas);
4299  else
4300  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value) << A->getAsString(Args) << Val;
4301  }
4302 
4303  // Parse -fsanitize= arguments.
4304  parseSanitizerKinds("-fsanitize=", Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_fsanitize_EQ),
4305  Diags, Opts.Sanitize);
4306  Opts.NoSanitizeFiles = Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_fsanitize_ignorelist_EQ);
4307  std::vector<std::string> systemIgnorelists =
4308  Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_fsanitize_system_ignorelist_EQ);
4309  Opts.NoSanitizeFiles.insert(Opts.NoSanitizeFiles.end(),
4310  systemIgnorelists.begin(),
4311  systemIgnorelists.end());
4312 
4313  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_fclang_abi_compat_EQ)) {
4314  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Latest);
4315 
4316  StringRef Ver = A->getValue();
4317  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> VerParts = Ver.split('.');
4318  unsigned Major, Minor = 0;
4319 
4320  // Check the version number is valid: either 3.x (0 <= x <= 9) or
4321  // y or y.0 (4 <= y <= current version).
4322  if (!VerParts.first.starts_with("0") &&
4323  !VerParts.first.getAsInteger(10, Major) && 3 <= Major &&
4324  Major <= CLANG_VERSION_MAJOR &&
4325  (Major == 3
4326  ? VerParts.second.size() == 1 &&
4327  !VerParts.second.getAsInteger(10, Minor)
4328  : VerParts.first.size() == Ver.size() || VerParts.second == "0")) {
4329  // Got a valid version number.
4330  if (Major == 3 && Minor <= 8)
4331  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver3_8);
4332  else if (Major <= 4)
4333  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver4);
4334  else if (Major <= 6)
4335  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver6);
4336  else if (Major <= 7)
4337  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver7);
4338  else if (Major <= 9)
4339  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver9);
4340  else if (Major <= 11)
4341  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver11);
4342  else if (Major <= 12)
4343  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver12);
4344  else if (Major <= 14)
4345  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver14);
4346  else if (Major <= 15)
4347  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver15);
4348  else if (Major <= 17)
4349  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver17);
4350  else if (Major <= 18)
4351  Opts.setClangABICompat(LangOptions::ClangABI::Ver18);
4352  } else if (Ver != "latest") {
4353  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
4354  << A->getAsString(Args) << A->getValue();
4355  }
4356  }
4357 
4358  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_msign_return_address_EQ)) {
4359  StringRef SignScope = A->getValue();
4360 
4361  if (SignScope.equals_insensitive("none"))
4362  Opts.setSignReturnAddressScope(
4363  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressScopeKind::None);
4364  else if (SignScope.equals_insensitive("all"))
4365  Opts.setSignReturnAddressScope(
4366  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressScopeKind::All);
4367  else if (SignScope.equals_insensitive("non-leaf"))
4368  Opts.setSignReturnAddressScope(
4369  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressScopeKind::NonLeaf);
4370  else
4371  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
4372  << A->getAsString(Args) << SignScope;
4373 
4374  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_msign_return_address_key_EQ)) {
4375  StringRef SignKey = A->getValue();
4376  if (!SignScope.empty() && !SignKey.empty()) {
4377  if (SignKey == "a_key")
4378  Opts.setSignReturnAddressKey(
4379  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressKeyKind::AKey);
4380  else if (SignKey == "b_key")
4381  Opts.setSignReturnAddressKey(
4382  LangOptions::SignReturnAddressKeyKind::BKey);
4383  else
4384  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_value)
4385  << A->getAsString(Args) << SignKey;
4386  }
4387  }
4388  }
4389 
4390  // The value can be empty, which indicates the system default should be used.
4391  StringRef CXXABI = Args.getLastArgValue(OPT_fcxx_abi_EQ);
4392  if (!CXXABI.empty()) {
4393  if (!TargetCXXABI::isABI(CXXABI)) {
4394  Diags.Report(diag::err_invalid_cxx_abi) << CXXABI;
4395  } else {
4396  auto Kind = TargetCXXABI::getKind(CXXABI);
4397  if (!TargetCXXABI::isSupportedCXXABI(T, Kind))
4398  Diags.Report(diag::err_unsupported_cxx_abi) << CXXABI << T.str();
4399  else
4400  Opts.CXXABI = Kind;
4401  }
4402  }
4403 
4404  Opts.RelativeCXXABIVTables =
4405  Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fexperimental_relative_cxx_abi_vtables,
4406  options::OPT_fno_experimental_relative_cxx_abi_vtables,
4407  TargetCXXABI::usesRelativeVTables(T));
4408 
4409  // RTTI is on by default.
4410  bool HasRTTI = !Args.hasArg(options::OPT_fno_rtti);
4411  Opts.OmitVTableRTTI =
4412  Args.hasFlag(options::OPT_fexperimental_omit_vtable_rtti,
4413  options::OPT_fno_experimental_omit_vtable_rtti, false);
4414  if (Opts.OmitVTableRTTI && HasRTTI)
4415  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_using_omit_rtti_component_without_no_rtti);
4416 
4417  for (const auto &A : Args.getAllArgValues(OPT_fmacro_prefix_map_EQ)) {
4418  auto Split = StringRef(A).split('=');
4419  Opts.MacroPrefixMap.insert(
4420  {std::string(Split.first), std::string(Split.second)});
4421  }
4422 
4423  Opts.UseTargetPathSeparator =
4424  !Args.getLastArg(OPT_fno_file_reproducible) &&
4425  (Args.getLastArg(OPT_ffile_compilation_dir_EQ) ||
4426  Args.getLastArg(OPT_fmacro_prefix_map_EQ) ||
4427  Args.getLastArg(OPT_ffile_reproducible));
4428 
4429  // Error if -mvscale-min is unbounded.
4430  if (Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(options::OPT_mvscale_min_EQ)) {
4431  unsigned VScaleMin;
4432  if (StringRef(A->getValue()).getAsInteger(10, VScaleMin) || VScaleMin == 0)
4433  Diags.Report(diag::err_cc1_unbounded_vscale_min);
4434  }
4435 
4436  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_frandomize_layout_seed_file_EQ)) {
4437  std::ifstream SeedFile(A->getValue(0));
4438 
4439  if (!SeedFile.is_open())
4440  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_cannot_open_randomize_layout_seed_file)
4441  << A->getValue(0);
4442 
4443  std::getline(SeedFile, Opts.RandstructSeed);
4444  }
4445 
4446  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_frandomize_layout_seed_EQ))
4447  Opts.RandstructSeed = A->getValue(0);
4448 
4449  // Validate options for HLSL
4450  if (Opts.HLSL) {
4451  // TODO: Revisit restricting SPIR-V to logical once we've figured out how to
4452  // handle PhysicalStorageBuffer64 memory model
4453  if (T.isDXIL() || T.isSPIRVLogical()) {
4454  enum { ShaderModel, VulkanEnv, ShaderStage };
4455  enum { OS, Environment };
4456 
4457  int ExpectedOS = T.isSPIRVLogical() ? VulkanEnv : ShaderModel;
4458 
4459  if (T.getOSName().empty()) {
4460  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_hlsl_bad_shader_required_in_target)
4461  << ExpectedOS << OS << T.str();
4462  } else if (T.getEnvironmentName().empty()) {
4463  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_hlsl_bad_shader_required_in_target)
4464  << ShaderStage << Environment << T.str();
4465  } else if (!T.isShaderStageEnvironment()) {
4466  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_hlsl_bad_shader_unsupported)
4467  << ShaderStage << T.getEnvironmentName() << T.str();
4468  }
4469 
4470  if (T.isDXIL()) {
4471  if (!T.isShaderModelOS() || T.getOSVersion() == VersionTuple(0)) {
4472  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_hlsl_bad_shader_unsupported)
4473  << ShaderModel << T.getOSName() << T.str();
4474  }
4475  // Validate that if fnative-half-type is given, that
4476  // the language standard is at least hlsl2018, and that
4477  // the target shader model is at least 6.2.
4478  if (Args.getLastArg(OPT_fnative_half_type)) {
4479  const LangStandard &Std =
4480  LangStandard::getLangStandardForKind(Opts.LangStd);
4481  if (!(Opts.LangStd >= LangStandard::lang_hlsl2018 &&
4482  T.getOSVersion() >= VersionTuple(6, 2)))
4483  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_hlsl_16bit_types_unsupported)
4484  << "-enable-16bit-types" << true << Std.getName()
4485  << T.getOSVersion().getAsString();
4486  }
4487  } else if (T.isSPIRVLogical()) {
4488  if (!T.isVulkanOS() || T.getVulkanVersion() == VersionTuple(0)) {
4489  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_hlsl_bad_shader_unsupported)
4490  << VulkanEnv << T.getOSName() << T.str();
4491  }
4492  if (Args.getLastArg(OPT_fnative_half_type)) {
4493  const LangStandard &Std =
4494  LangStandard::getLangStandardForKind(Opts.LangStd);
4495  if (!(Opts.LangStd >= LangStandard::lang_hlsl2018))
4496  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_hlsl_16bit_types_unsupported)
4497  << "-fnative-half-type" << false << Std.getName();
4498  }
4499  } else {
4500  llvm_unreachable("expected DXIL or SPIR-V target");
4501  }
4502  } else
4503  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_hlsl_unsupported_target) << T.str();
4504  }
4505 
4506  // GPURelocatableDeviceCode should be true for SYCL if not specified.
4507  if (Args.hasArg(OPT_fsycl_is_device) || Args.hasArg(OPT_fsycl_is_host))
4508  Opts.GPURelocatableDeviceCode = Args.hasFlag(
4509  options::OPT_fgpu_rdc, options::OPT_fno_gpu_rdc, /*default=*/true);
4510 
4511  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
4512 }
4513 
4514 static bool isStrictlyPreprocessorAction(frontend::ActionKind Action) {
4515  switch (Action) {
4516  case frontend::ASTDeclList:
4517  case frontend::ASTDump:
4518  case frontend::ASTPrint:
4519  case frontend::ASTView:
4520  case frontend::EmitAssembly:
4521  case frontend::EmitBC:
4522  case frontend::EmitHTML:
4523  case frontend::EmitLLVM:
4524  case frontend::EmitLLVMOnly:
4525  case frontend::EmitCodeGenOnly:
4526  case frontend::EmitObj:
4527  case frontend::ExtractAPI:
4528  case frontend::FixIt:
4529  case frontend::GenerateModule:
4530  case frontend::GenerateModuleInterface:
4531  case frontend::GenerateReducedModuleInterface:
4532  case frontend::GenerateHeaderUnit:
4533  case frontend::GeneratePCH:
4534  case frontend::GenerateInterfaceStubs:
4535  case frontend::ParseSyntaxOnly:
4536  case frontend::ModuleFileInfo:
4537  case frontend::VerifyPCH:
4538  case frontend::PluginAction:
4539  case frontend::RewriteObjC:
4540  case frontend::RewriteTest:
4541  case frontend::RunAnalysis:
4542  case frontend::TemplightDump:
4543  case frontend::MigrateSource:
4544  return false;
4545 
4546  case frontend::DumpCompilerOptions:
4547  case frontend::DumpRawTokens:
4548  case frontend::DumpTokens:
4549  case frontend::InitOnly:
4550  case frontend::PrintPreamble:
4551  case frontend::PrintPreprocessedInput:
4552  case frontend::RewriteMacros:
4553  case frontend::RunPreprocessorOnly:
4554  case frontend::PrintDependencyDirectivesSourceMinimizerOutput:
4555  return true;
4556  }
4557  llvm_unreachable("invalid frontend action");
4558 }
4559 
4560 static void GeneratePreprocessorArgs(const PreprocessorOptions &Opts,
4561  ArgumentConsumer Consumer,
4562  const LangOptions &LangOpts,
4563  const FrontendOptions &FrontendOpts,
4564  const CodeGenOptions &CodeGenOpts) {
4565  const PreprocessorOptions *PreprocessorOpts = &Opts;
4566 
4567 #define PREPROCESSOR_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(...) \
4568  GENERATE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(Consumer, __VA_ARGS__)
4569 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
4570 #undef PREPROCESSOR_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
4571 
4572  if (Opts.PCHWithHdrStop && !Opts.PCHWithHdrStopCreate)
4573  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_pch_through_hdrstop_use);
4574 
4575  for (const auto &D : Opts.DeserializedPCHDeclsToErrorOn)
4576  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_error_on_deserialized_pch_decl, D);
4577 
4578  if (Opts.PrecompiledPreambleBytes != std::make_pair(0u, false))
4579  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_preamble_bytes_EQ,
4580  Twine(Opts.PrecompiledPreambleBytes.first) + "," +
4581  (Opts.PrecompiledPreambleBytes.second ? "1" : "0"));
4582 
4583  for (const auto &M : Opts.Macros) {
4584  // Don't generate __CET__ macro definitions. They are implied by the
4585  // -fcf-protection option that is generated elsewhere.
4586  if (M.first == "__CET__=1" && !M.second &&
4587  !CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionReturn && CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionBranch)
4588  continue;
4589  if (M.first == "__CET__=2" && !M.second && CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionReturn &&
4590  !CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionBranch)
4591  continue;
4592  if (M.first == "__CET__=3" && !M.second && CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionReturn &&
4593  CodeGenOpts.CFProtectionBranch)
4594  continue;
4595 
4596  GenerateArg(Consumer, M.second ? OPT_U : OPT_D, M.first);
4597  }
4598 
4599  for (const auto &I : Opts.Includes) {
4600  // Don't generate OpenCL includes. They are implied by other flags that are
4601  // generated elsewhere.
4602  if (LangOpts.OpenCL && LangOpts.IncludeDefaultHeader &&
4603  ((LangOpts.DeclareOpenCLBuiltins && I == "opencl-c-base.h") ||
4604  I == "opencl-c.h"))
4605  continue;
4606  // Don't generate HLSL includes. They are implied by other flags that are
4607  // generated elsewhere.
4608  if (LangOpts.HLSL && I == "hlsl.h")
4609  continue;
4610 
4611  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_include, I);
4612  }
4613 
4614  for (const auto &CI : Opts.ChainedIncludes)
4615  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_chain_include, CI);
4616 
4617  for (const auto &RF : Opts.RemappedFiles)
4618  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_remap_file, RF.first + ";" + RF.second);
4619 
4620  if (Opts.SourceDateEpoch)
4621  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_source_date_epoch, Twine(*Opts.SourceDateEpoch));
4622 
4623  if (Opts.DefineTargetOSMacros)
4624  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fdefine_target_os_macros);
4625 
4626  // Don't handle LexEditorPlaceholders. It is implied by the action that is
4627  // generated elsewhere.
4628 }
4629 
4630 static bool ParsePreprocessorArgs(PreprocessorOptions &Opts, ArgList &Args,
4631  DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
4632  frontend::ActionKind Action,
4633  const FrontendOptions &FrontendOpts) {
4634  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
4635 
4636  PreprocessorOptions *PreprocessorOpts = &Opts;
4637 
4638 #define PREPROCESSOR_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(...) \
4639  PARSE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(Args, Diags, __VA_ARGS__)
4640 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
4641 #undef PREPROCESSOR_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
4642 
4643  Opts.PCHWithHdrStop = Args.hasArg(OPT_pch_through_hdrstop_create) ||
4644  Args.hasArg(OPT_pch_through_hdrstop_use);
4645 
4646  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_error_on_deserialized_pch_decl))
4647  Opts.DeserializedPCHDeclsToErrorOn.insert(A->getValue());
4648 
4649  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_preamble_bytes_EQ)) {
4650  StringRef Value(A->getValue());
4651  size_t Comma = Value.find(',');
4652  unsigned Bytes = 0;
4653  unsigned EndOfLine = 0;
4654 
4655  if (Comma == StringRef::npos ||
4656  Value.substr(0, Comma).getAsInteger(10, Bytes) ||
4657  Value.substr(Comma + 1).getAsInteger(10, EndOfLine))
4658  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_preamble_format);
4659  else {
4660  Opts.PrecompiledPreambleBytes.first = Bytes;
4661  Opts.PrecompiledPreambleBytes.second = (EndOfLine != 0);
4662  }
4663  }
4664 
4665  // Add the __CET__ macro if a CFProtection option is set.
4666  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_fcf_protection_EQ)) {
4667  StringRef Name = A->getValue();
4668  if (Name == "branch")
4669  Opts.addMacroDef("__CET__=1");
4670  else if (Name == "return")
4671  Opts.addMacroDef("__CET__=2");
4672  else if (Name == "full")
4673  Opts.addMacroDef("__CET__=3");
4674  }
4675 
4676  // Add macros from the command line.
4677  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_D, OPT_U)) {
4678  if (A->getOption().matches(OPT_D))
4679  Opts.addMacroDef(A->getValue());
4680  else
4681  Opts.addMacroUndef(A->getValue());
4682  }
4683 
4684  // Add the ordered list of -includes.
4685  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_include))
4686  Opts.Includes.emplace_back(A->getValue());
4687 
4688  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_chain_include))
4689  Opts.ChainedIncludes.emplace_back(A->getValue());
4690 
4691  for (const auto *A : Args.filtered(OPT_remap_file)) {
4692  std::pair<StringRef, StringRef> Split = StringRef(A->getValue()).split(';');
4693 
4694  if (Split.second.empty()) {
4695  Diags.Report(diag::err_drv_invalid_remap_file) << A->getAsString(Args);
4696  continue;
4697  }
4698 
4699  Opts.addRemappedFile(Split.first, Split.second);
4700  }
4701 
4702  if (const Arg *A = Args.getLastArg(OPT_source_date_epoch)) {
4703  StringRef Epoch = A->getValue();
4704  // SOURCE_DATE_EPOCH, if specified, must be a non-negative decimal integer.
4705  // On time64 systems, pick 253402300799 (the UNIX timestamp of
4706  // 9999-12-31T23:59:59Z) as the upper bound.
4707  const uint64_t MaxTimestamp =
4708  std::min<uint64_t>(std::numeric_limits<time_t>::max(), 253402300799);
4709  uint64_t V;
4710  if (Epoch.getAsInteger(10, V) || V > MaxTimestamp) {
4711  Diags.Report(diag::err_fe_invalid_source_date_epoch)
4712  << Epoch << MaxTimestamp;
4713  } else {
4714  Opts.SourceDateEpoch = V;
4715  }
4716  }
4717 
4718  // Always avoid lexing editor placeholders when we're just running the
4719  // preprocessor as we never want to emit the
4720  // "editor placeholder in source file" error in PP only mode.
4721  if (isStrictlyPreprocessorAction(Action))
4722  Opts.LexEditorPlaceholders = false;
4723 
4724  Opts.DefineTargetOSMacros =
4725  Args.hasFlag(OPT_fdefine_target_os_macros,
4726  OPT_fno_define_target_os_macros, Opts.DefineTargetOSMacros);
4727 
4728  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
4729 }
4730 
4731 static void
4732 GeneratePreprocessorOutputArgs(const PreprocessorOutputOptions &Opts,
4733  ArgumentConsumer Consumer,
4734  frontend::ActionKind Action) {
4735  const PreprocessorOutputOptions &PreprocessorOutputOpts = Opts;
4736 
4737 #define PREPROCESSOR_OUTPUT_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(...) \
4738  GENERATE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(Consumer, __VA_ARGS__)
4739 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
4740 #undef PREPROCESSOR_OUTPUT_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
4741 
4742  bool Generate_dM = isStrictlyPreprocessorAction(Action) && !Opts.ShowCPP;
4743  if (Generate_dM)
4744  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_dM);
4745  if (!Generate_dM && Opts.ShowMacros)
4746  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_dD);
4747  if (Opts.DirectivesOnly)
4748  GenerateArg(Consumer, OPT_fdirectives_only);
4749 }
4750 
4751 static bool ParsePreprocessorOutputArgs(PreprocessorOutputOptions &Opts,
4752  ArgList &Args, DiagnosticsEngine &Diags,
4753  frontend::ActionKind Action) {
4754  unsigned NumErrorsBefore = Diags.getNumErrors();
4755 
4756  PreprocessorOutputOptions &PreprocessorOutputOpts = Opts;
4757 
4758 #define PREPROCESSOR_OUTPUT_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(...) \
4759  PARSE_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING(Args, Diags, __VA_ARGS__)
4760 #include "clang/Driver/Options.inc"
4761 #undef PREPROCESSOR_OUTPUT_OPTION_WITH_MARSHALLING
4762 
4763  Opts.ShowCPP = isStrictlyPreprocessorAction(Action) && !Args.hasArg(OPT_dM);
4764  Opts.ShowMacros = Args.hasArg(OPT_dM) || Args.hasArg(OPT_dD);
4765  Opts.DirectivesOnly = Args.hasArg(OPT_fdirectives_only);
4766 
4767  return Diags.getNumErrors() == NumErrorsBefore;
4768 }
